description: This is a strong area because the job description mentions C# and .NET as primary development languages. While C++ and Python are not directly mentioned, the candidate's proficiency in multiple languages demonstrates adaptability and a broader understanding of programming concepts. JavaScript and Typescript would be useful in this role since they are working with web applications, it shows that they have experience and knowledge about it.

This is a strong area as it showcases experience with modern web development frameworks and UI design tools. While the job description focuses on C# and .NET, having skills in Reactjs and TailwindCSS is valuable for developing user interfaces and front-end components, showing a well-rounded skillset.

This is a strong area. The candidate's repeated experience as a Frontend Developer, as shown in the Health Recommendation System, TikTok TechJam, and EvoGym projects, highlights their focus and expertise in this area. This direct experience is highly relevant to the Software Engineer I role, which involves system/configuration support and software development.

This is a strong area, as the candidate's involvement in the Google Developer Group as a Web Specialist shows initiative and a commitment to continuous learning. This implies a willingness to share knowledge and collaborate with others, which are important qualities for the role, as it requires strong communication skills and collaboration within a team.

This is a weak area because the candidate is expected to graduate in June 2027, implying they are currently a student. The job description seeks someone with formal software education *and/or* a ton of practical experience. While the projects indicate some practical experience, the CV doesn't highlight enough extensive practical experience to compensate for the lack of a completed degree. The candidate could improve this by detailing more extensive projects or internships that demonstrate significant practical experience.

This is a weak area as the project description is vague and doesn't provide enough detail about the technical challenges faced or the candidate's specific contributions. The description focuses on the general purpose of the website but lacks specifics about the architecture, algorithms, or specific features implemented. To improve this, the candidate could elaborate on the complexities of the AI integration, the data structures used, or any optimization techniques applied. Also how he/she handle the backend data.

This is a weak area as it lacks depth. While the candidate mentions creating a solution to enhance Tailored Discovery, the description is brief and lacks technical details. There's no mention of the specific technologies or algorithms used to extract user preferences, the architecture of the solution, or any performance optimizations implemented. To improve this, the candidate could provide more details about the technical aspects of the project and quantify the impact of their solution on user engagement or sales.

This is a weak area as it is clearly stated that the project is from a tutorial video. While it demonstrates the candidate's ability to follow instructions and implement a given design, it doesn't showcase independent problem-solving or innovation. This project doesn't effectively demonstrate the candidate's ability to design and develop a solution from scratch. The project is not related to public health or safety mentioned in the job description. Consider highlighting projects where they took the initiative to solve a problem or create something original.
